select  
  ref_3.cd_credit_rating as c0, 
  ref_4.P_COMMENT as c1, 
  ref_3.cd_dep_count as c2, 
  ref_1.c_mktsegment as c3, 
  ref_3.cd_gender as c4, 
  case when (true) 
      and (ref_1.c_custkey >= ref_1.c_custkey) then ref_4.P_CONTAINER else ref_4.P_CONTAINER end
     as c5, 
  ref_3.cd_dep_college_count as c6, 
  ref_1.c_custkey as c7, 
  ref_1.c_custkey as c8, 
  ref_2.value as c9, 
  case when (ref_1.c_city > ref_1.c_city) 
      or ((ref_2.value >= ref_2.value) 
        and (ref_3.cd_gender < ref_3.cd_marital_status)) then rand() else rand() end
     as c10, 
  ref_4.P_COMMENT as c11
from 
  sqlsmith.tpcds_100g_web_page as ref_0
          inner join sqlsmith.ssb_100g_customer as ref_1
          on (ref_0.wp_url = ref_1.c_name )
        right join sqlsmith.metrics_detail as ref_2
        on (ref_1.c_custkey = ref_2.tags_id )
      inner join sqlsmith.tpcds_100g_customer_demographics as ref_3
      on (ref_1.c_mktsegment = ref_3.cd_gender )
    right join sqlsmith.tpch_100g_part as ref_4
    on (ref_1.c_nation = ref_4.P_NAME )
where ref_0.wp_creation_date_sk < ref_2.tags_id
limit 102;
